AC  GenProp0061
DE  Lipoprotein system lgt/lsp/lnt
TP  SYSTEM
AU  Haft D
TH  0
CC  Some membrane proteins are anchored to the membrane by a lipid moiety 
CC  attached to a modified N-terminus rather than by a transmembrane 
CC  helix. This property describes such a system. The system starts with 
CC  the modification of the Cys sulfhydryl of the conserved lipobox motif 
CC  L-X-G/A-C by prolipoprotein diacylglyceryl transferase (Lgt). 
CC  Prolipoprotein signal peptidase (Lsp) then cleaves the lipoprotein 
CC  signal sequence leaving Cys as the new N-terminal residue. Finally 
CC  the Cys NH2 is acylated by apolipoprotein N-acyltransferase (Lnt). 
--
